      = [[FC Augsburg]]\n| caps13         = 18\n| goals13        = 0 \n| years14        = 2013\u20132014\n| clubs14        = \u2192 [[Fortuna D\u00fcsseldorf]] (loan)\n| caps14         = 10\n| goals14        = 2\n| years15        = 2014\n| clubs15        = [[Helsingin Jalkapalloklubi|HJK Helsinki]]  \n| caps15         = 4\n| goals15        = 1\n| years16        = 2015\n| clubs16        = [[FC Irtysh Pavlodar|Irtysh Pavlodar]]\n| caps16         = 11\n| goals16        = 2\n| years17        = 2015\u20132016\n| clubs17        = [[Chippa United F.C.|Chippa United]]\n| caps17         = 14\n| goals17        = 3\n| years18        = 2016\n| clubs18        = [[Riga FC|Riga]]\n| caps18         = 8\n| goals18        = 1\n| years19        = 2016\u20132017\n| clubs19        = [[ASEC Mimosas]]\n| caps19         = 26\n| goals19        = 13\n| years20        = 2017\u20132018\n| clubs20        = [[Al-Masry SC|Al-Masry]]\n| caps20         = 19\n| goals20        = 8\n| years21        = 2019\n| clubs21        = [[US des Forces Arm\u00e9es]]\n| caps21         = \n| goals21        = \n| years22        = 2019\u2013\n| clubs22        = [[Horoya AC]]\n| caps22         = \n| goals22        = \n| nationalyears1 = 2003\u2013\n| nationalteam1  = [[Burkina Faso national football team|Burkina Faso]]\n| nationalcaps1  = 79\n| nationalgoals1 = 24\n| pcupdate       = 7 February 2019\n| ntupdate       = 14 November 2019\n}}\n\n'''Aristide Banc\u00e9''' (born 19 September 1984) is a [[Burkina Faso|Burkinab\u00e9]] professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[Forward (association football)#Striker|striker]] for [[Horoya AC]] and the [[Burkina Faso national football team|Burkina Faso national team]].\n\n==Club career==\n\n===HJK Helsinki===\nIn September 2014, Banc\u00e9 signed with Finnish [[Veikkausliiga]] side [[Helsingin Jalkapalloklubi|HJK Helsinki]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Aristide Banc\u00e9 per l'HJK Helsinki|url=http://sport.virgilio.it/notizie/calcio/calciomercato/2014/09/02/aristide-bance-per-l-hjk-helsinki-1040789|publisher=Virgilio Sport|date=2 September 2014|accessdate=3 September 2014|language=it|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140907044422/http://sport.virgilio.it/notizie/calcio/calciomercato/2014/09/02/aristide-bance-per-l-hjk-helsinki-1040789|archive-date=7 September 2014|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\n===Irtysh Pavlodar===\nIn February 2015, Banc\u00e9 signed for [[Kazakhstan Premier League]] side [[FC Irtysh Pavlodar]],<ref>{{cite web|script-title=ru:\u0424\u043e\u0440\u0432\u0430\u0440\u0434 \u0441\u0431\u043e\u0440\u043d\u043e\u0439 \u0411\u0443\u0440\u043a\u0438\u043d\u0430-\u0424\u0430\u0441\u043e \u043f\u0435\u0440\u0435\u0448\u0435\u043b \u0432 \u0418\u0440\u0442\u044b\u0448|url=http://sports.kz/news/forvard-sbornoy-burkina-faso-pereshel-v-irtyish|website=sports.kz|accessdate=26 February 2015|language=Russian|date=26 February 2015}}</ref> leaving the club in June of the same year.<ref>{{cite web|script-title=ru:\u0410\u0440\u0438\u0441\u0442\u0438\u0434 \u0411\u0430\u043d\u0441\u0435 \u043f\u043e\u043a\u0438\u043d\u0443\u043b \u0418\u0440\u0442\u044b\u0448|url=http://vesti.kz/kazfutbol/206107/|website=vesti.kz|publisher=Vesti|accessdate=21 November 2016|language=Russian|date=21 June 2015}}</ref>\n\n===Chippa United===\nIn August 2015, Banc\u00e9 went on trial with [[Bidvest Wits F.C.|Bidvest Wits]] of the South African [[Premier Soccer League]],<ref>{{cite web|title=Bance Training With Wits|url=http://www.soccerladuma.co.za/news/articles/categories/south-africa/bance-on-trial-at-bidvest-wits/215480|website=Soccer Laduma|accessdate=12 August 2015|date=12 August 2015}}</ref> eventually signing with [[Chippa United FC|Chippa United]] later in the month.<ref>{{cite web|title=Chippa United confirm the signing of former Bundesliga striker Aristide Bance|url=http://www.goal.com/en-za/news/4682/transfer-zone/2015/08/14/14424662/chippa-united-confirm-the-signing-of-former-bundesliga|website=goal.com|publisher=Goal|accessdate=21 November 2016|date=14 August 2015}}</ref> Banc\u00e9 parted company with Chippa United in May 2016.<ref>{{cite web|title=Aristide Bance has up and left Chippa United|url=http://www.kickoff.com/news/65152/aristide-bance-has-up-and-left-chippa-united|website=kickoff.com|publisher=Kickoff|accessdate=21 November 2016|date=10 May 2016}}</ref>\n\n===Riga===\nIn August 2016, Banc\u00e9 signed with [[Latvian Higher League|Virsl\u012bga]] side [[Riga FC]].<ref>{{cite web|title=L\u2019international burkinab\u00e8 Aristide Banc\u00e9 signe au Riga FC (Lettonie)|url=http://news.aouaga.com/h/101461.html|website=news.aouaga.com|publisher=AOuaga|accessdate=21 November 2016|language=French|date=22 August 2016}}</ref>\n\n===ASEC Mimosas===\nIn November 2016, Banc\u00e9 was confirmed as a new signing for Ivorian side [[ASEC Mimosas]].<ref>{{cite web|title=LES RECRUES DE LA LIGNE D\u2019ATTAQUE|url=http://www.asec.ci/fr/2016/11/16/les_recrues_de_la_ligne_dattaque/|website=asec.ci|publisher=ASEC Mimosas|accessdate=19 September 2017|language=French|date=16 November 2016}}</ref> Banc\u00e9 was voted player of the month for November 2016.<ref>[http://www.voaafrique.com/a/aristide-bance-elu-meilleur-joueur-du-mois-de-novembre/3656063.html Championnat de C\u00f4te d'Ivoire - Aristide Banc\u00e9 \u00e9lu meilleur joueur du mois de novembre]\u201a voaafrique.com</ref>\n\n===Al-Masry===\nIn July 2017, Banc\u00e9 signed a two-year contract with [[Egyptian Premier League]] side [[Al-Masry SC|Al-Masry]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Burkina Faso star Aristide Bance moves to Egypt's Al Masry|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/40618717|website=bbc.co.uk|publisher=BBC Sport|accessdate=19 September 2017|date=16 July 2017}}</ref> \n\n===US des Forces Arm\u00e9es===\nIn February 2019, Banc\u00e9 returned to Burkina Faso to sign for [[US des Forces Arm\u00e9es]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/47170589|title=Striker Aristide Bance returns to play in Burkina Faso|date=8 February 2019|website=BBC Sport|accessdate=28 August 2019|first=Mohamed Fajah|last=Barrie}}</ref>\n\n===Horoya AC===\nIn May 2019, Banc\u00e9 signed for Guinean club [[Horoya AC]], his 22nd team.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/48444286|title=Burkina Faso's Aristide Bance makes Guinea's Horoya his 22nd club|date=29 May 2019|website=BBC Sport|accessdate=28 August 2019}}</ref> In October 2019 he scored a hate-trick in the Confederation Cup play-offs.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/50207511|title=Aristide Bance stars for Horoya in Confederation Cup play-offs|date=28 October 2019|via=www.bbc.co.uk}}</ref>\n\n==International career==\nBanc\u00e9 is a member of the [[Burkina Faso national football team]].<ref>{{cite web | url = http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport2/hi/football/africa/8436051.stm | title =  Bance missing for Burkina Faso | publisher = BBC Sport | accessdate = 3 April 2010 | date = 31 December 2009}}</ref> He has appeared for Burkina Faso at three [[Africa Cup of Nations]] tournaments, scoring both the team's goal and the winning kick in the [[penalty shoot-out (association football)|penalty shootout]] in ''Les \u00c9talons''' semi-final defeat of [[Ghana national football team|Ghana]] at the [[2013 Africa Cup of Nations|2013 edition]] to put the nation in the final for first time in its history.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/0/football/21339090|title=Burkina Faso 1-1 Ghana|accessdate=26 January 2015|work=BBC}}</ref> Burkina Faso went on to lose the final to [[Nigeria national football team|Nigeria]] and finish as runner-up.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/0/football/21396138|title=Nigeria 1-0 Burkina Faso|accessdate=26 January 2015|work=BBC}}</ref>\n\nAt the [[2015 Africa Cup of Nations]], Banc\u00e9 scored Burkina Faso's goal in a 2\u20131 loss to [[Congo national football team|Congo]] which saw the 2013 runner-up knocked out at the group stage.<ref>{{cite news|title=Congo 2-1 Burkina Faso|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/football/30868924|accessdate=26 January 2015|work=BBC Sport|date=25 January 2015}}</ref> In [[2017 Africa Cup of Nations|2017]], he scored a crucial goal in his team's quarter-final against [[Tunisia]] and in the semi-final scored a late equaliser against [[Egypt]] to take the game to a penalty shootout. Burkina Faso lost the shootout and eventually finished third overall in the cup, defeating [[Ghana]] in the third-place playoff.\n\n==Personal life==\nBanc\u00e9 was born in [[Abidjan]], Ivory Coast, but moved to Burkina Faso as a child. He is the brother-in-law to professional footballer [[Aruna Dindane]].<ref>{{cite web | url = http://www.bild.de/BILD/sport/fussball/zweite-liga/2009/02/24/mainz-05/aristide-bance-das-tor-gespenst.html | title = Das Tor-Gespenst | publisher = Bild | language = German | accessdate = 3 April 2010 | date = 23 February 2009}}</ref>\n\n==Career statistics==\n\n===International===\n{{Updated|match played 26 March 2018}}<ref name=\"NFT\">{{NFT player|id=11183|name=Aristide Banc\u00e9|accessdate=17 November 2015}}</ref>\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|-\n|colspan=\"3\"|[[Burkina Faso national football team|Burkina Faso]]\n|-\n!Year!!Apps!!Goals\n|-\n|2003||1||0\n|-\n|2004||0||0\n|-\n|2005||2||0\n|-\n|2006||2||0\n|-\n|2007||2||0\n|-\n|2008||1||1\n|-\n|2009||5||1\n|-\n|2010||3||0\n|-\n|2011||5||2\n|-\n|2012||5||1\n|-\n|2013||13||5\n|-\n|2014||6||1\n|-\n|2015||11||6\n|-\n|2016||4||0\n|-\n|2017||11||4\n|-\n|2018||2||1\n|-\n|2018||6||2\n|-\n!Total||79||24\n|}\n\n===International goals===\n:''Scores and results list Burkina Faso's goal tally first.''<ref name=\"NFT\"/>\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n! No !! Date !! Venue !! Opponent !! Score !! Result !! Competition\n|-\n| 1. || 12 October 2008 || [[Prince Louis Rwagasore Stadium]], [[Bujumbura]], Burundi || {{flag|Burundi}} || align=center | '''1'''\u20130 || align=center | 3\u20131 || [[2010 FIFA World Cup qualification \u2013 CAF Second Round|2